  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to be properly notified about possible errors while filling in forms, so I can properly use Status desktop.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\nThere are different instances where the user needs to fill in information that we need to validate.\r\nInstances:\r\n- Onboarding (sign in/sign up/recover account)\r\n- New 1:1 chat > contact code\r\n- New public chat > topic name\r\n\r\n*Pre-conditions*:\r\nIn order to validate forms for onboarding, #4418 needs to be implemented first.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nWhen the user fills in a form with information, we need to validate it -when possible- inline.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nValidation is not consistent yet. Examples:\r\n<img width=\"656\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-08-20 a la s 8 47 21 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/44372466-629b0900-a4ba-11e8-939e-747e96c6bf97.png\">\r\nContact code format is not validated.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"663\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-08-20 a la s 8 47 53 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/44372479-72b2e880-a4ba-11e8-9fb3-e1c574294a8a.png\">\r\nWrong topic name format doesn't explain why the button is disabled.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Click on \"+\" button to start a new chat\r\n- Write a contact code with an invalid format (anything that doesn't start with 0x...) or write a topic name with special characters.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nDesign and cases here >> zpl.io/bAEEv3B (Zeplin, needs permissions)\r\nExample:\r\n<img width=\"822\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-08-20 a la s 8 52 44 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/44372593-0be1ff00-a4bb-11e8-88a4-c3b5ff3acc18.png\">\r\n\r\n",
